decision_conditions:
The Planning Inspectorate allow the appeal made under Section 20 of the Planning (Listed Buildings and Conservation Areas) Act 1990 and grant listed building consent for internal alterations and refurbishment; creation of one x 2 bedroomed maisonette in basement and ground floor and three x 1 bedroomed flats on first , second and third floors at 288 Essex Road, London, N1, in accordance with the terms of the application reference: P031317 dated 19th June 2000 and the plans submitted therewith, subject to the following conditions:

1.  the works herbey permitted shall be commenced before the expiration of five years from the date of this decision;

2.  internal and external works shall be carried out in materials of a colour and texture and with architectural details to match those existing;

3.  before the works hereby permitted are commenced, detailed drawings of the following to a scale of not less than 1:10 (but with glazing bars additionally shown at full size):

a.  staircases includign balustrades;
b.  all new internal joinery;
c. windows

shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority and the works shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details.

4.  Before the works hereby permitted are commenced, details of those areas to be finished with traditional lime plaster shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority and the works shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details.

5.  No vents, flues or pipes shall be fixed to the front elevation of the building without the prior written approval of the Local Planning Authority.

6.  Notwithstanding the layout of partitiions shown on the floor plans included in the application plans, before the works hereby permitted are commenced, details of a scheme showing revised alignment of the internal partitions at all floor levels shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the Local Planning Authority and the works shall be carried out in accordance with the approved details.
